    {
      "type": "grammar_spotlight",
      "content": "In the poem above, look at **かけたる** (*kake-taru*). \n1. **かけ** (*kake*) is the verb 'to stake/hang'.\n2. **たる** (*taru*) is the 'attributive' form of *tari*.\n\nBecause it is in the *Rentaikei* (attributive) form, it modifies the noun **かけろふ** (mayfly). It doesn't just mean the mayfly 'staked' its life in the past; it means the mayfly is currently in the state of having its life staked. \n\n**Logic Check:** \nAction: *kake* (stake) + Existence: *ari* = *kake-tari* (is in the state of having staked).",
      "evidence": "See the poem above."
    },
