    {
      "type": "contrast_example",
      "content": "In Poem 2, we see **なつけたり** (*natsuketari*). Here, *tari* is in its conclusive form (*Shūshikei*). It ends the first thought. \n\nIf the poet used **なつけつ** (*natsuketsu* - using the perfective *tsu*), it would mean 'Someone finished naming it.' \nBy using **なつけたり** (*natsuketari*), it means 'It has been named (and that name sticks to it now).'"
